'' when she told him that his chief of staff had hung up on her twice. `` He did n't know about the hanging up the first time, because I did n't tell him,'' she said. `` The second time, I told him.'' Mrs. <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> charged that <PERSON> Regan </PERSON> `` did n't tell the truth'' in his book and said that she intended to `` tell everything _ everything the way it really happened'' in her memoirs, due to be published later this year. <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> also was asked about reports that his administration had recently considered attacking a Libyan plant that is believed to be producing chemical weapons. `` I never like to talk about what the options might be that are considered in anything of that kind ... And no, we had _ we were not planning such an option,'' the president said.
