<HEAD>Mudslide Knocks House Off Foundations; Others Evacuated</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. ALBANS, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An early morning mudslide that `` looked like lava'' pushed a house 10 feet off its foundation Tuesday and forced authorities to evacuate 10 other homes, officials said. `` I've got chest-high mud in what used to be my back yard,'' said <PERSON> Robey </PERSON> <PERSON> Kaufman </PERSON>, whose $ 100,000 home was destroyed. The hill into which the house was built began shifting late Monday night for reasons still unclear Tuesday, but water from a broken main behind the house might have loosened the mud, said <LOCATION> Kanawha </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> Public Safety Director <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Wolford </PERSON>. `` It was like a wall of mud,'' <ORGANIZATION> Wolford </ORGANIZATION> said. `` The fire chief out there said it looked like lava.'' Mud from the hill piled up against the back of the house and the pressure collapsed the basement, slowly pushing the house off its foundation and into the front yard, <ORGANIZATION> Wolford </ORGANIZATION> said. The <ORGANIZATION> Kaufmans </ORGANIZATION> `` apparently heard the house making some unusual popping and cracking noises. They finally decided they should get out of there,'' he said. By the time authorities were called, 12:30 a.m., the house was off its foundation. Gas, water and electical lines had been severed, <ORGANIZATION> Wolford </ORGANIZATION> said. As a precaution, authorities asked people living in the 10 other houses on the dead-end street to leave for a few hours. The Kaufmans are staying with neighbors, <ORGANIZATION> Wolford </ORGANIZATION> said.
