<HEAD>Woman Identified as Mental Patient</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A woman found four days ago wandering through a deserted shopping center has been identified as a patient from a British mental hospital, police said Tuesday. Police remained puzzled by how she managed to get to <LOCATION> Heathrow </LOCATION> airport and board a plane, apparently without money or a passport, said Inspector <PERSON> Kjell </PERSON> <PERSON> Bergstrom </PERSON>. The 22-year-old woman, <PERSON> Karen </PERSON> <PERSON> Ponsford </PERSON>, first was reported to be a deaf-mute because she refused to talk. A Swedish police patrol picked her up at 3 a.m. Saturday in a shopping mall north of <LOCATION> Stockholm </LOCATION>. She was believed to have walked six miles from <LOCATION> Arlanda </LOCATION> airport carrying nothing but a doll, officials said.
