<TEXT>
 An explosion in a coal mine in eastern <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> killed 11 people, an official report said Tuesday. The <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> Daily said 14 people were recovering from carbon monoxide poisoning suffered in the blast Saturday at a small mine in <LOCATION> Anhui </LOCATION> province. Hundreds of people are killed each year in accidents in <LOCATION> Chinese </LOCATION> coal mines, many of them small, locally run operations that lack safety equipment and proper training for workers. Last month, the press reported 13 miners in central <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Hebei </LOCATION> province had emergency oxygen tanks but suffocated because they did not know how to use the equipment.
