<HEAD>Still Turned On Because No Money to Pay for Storage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DELANO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Christmas decorations still glow each night in downtown Delano. It's not that residents remain captivated by the holiday; it's just that the <ORGANIZATION> Chamber </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> does n't have enough money to store the decorations and pay for insurance coverage Because of the lack of funds, the chamber's board voted against renewing a contract to have a Fresno-area firm store the green and red decorations. They have been plugged into city lightpoles since mid-November, so the lights turn on automatically every evening. `` It's very embarrassing to me,'' Chamber Manager <PERSON> Dorothy </PERSON> <PERSON> Knight </PERSON> said on Monday. `` It's bad for the image of the community.''
