<HEAD>Guerrillas Attack In Northern Province</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Leftist guerrillas Tuesday launched coordinated attacks on military positions in six northern towns, the armed forces and the rebels reported. The armed forces said three rebels were killed and three soldiers wounded in the battles before dawn in the northern province of <LOCATION> Chalatenango </LOCATION>. The guerrillas said they caused 25 casualties among army troops, but did not specify the number of dead and wounded. The rebels, who commented on the clandestine Radio <PERSON> Farbundo </PERSON> <PERSON> Marti </PERSON>, did not mention their own losses. The radio, like the Marxist-led <ORGANIZATION> Farabundo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marti </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION> that has been battling the U.S.-backed government for nine years, is named for a 1930s revolutionary. The armed forces press office, as well as the clandestine guerrilla radio, reported fighting in and around the towns of <PERSON> Dulce </PERSON> <PERSON> Nombre </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Maria </PERSON>, <LOCATION> El </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Refugio </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> La </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Laguna </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ignacio </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Miguel </LOCATION> de Mercedes. The rebels also staged what the army called `` harassment'' attacks on positions around the 4th Infantry Brigade headquarters at <LOCATION> El </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Paraiso </LOCATION>, 28 miles north of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Salvador </LOCATION>, the capital. The insurgents said the coordinated attacks were part of an operation called `` In response to repression, the people and militias prepare the insurrection.'' Rebel forces also blew up three utility posts near <LOCATION> Apopa </LOCATION>, seven miles north of the capital, causing temporary blackouts in the capital and some northern sectors of the country.
