<HEAD>L.F. Rothschild Quits As Primary Dealer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> L.F. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rothschild </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Co.. Tuesday said it voluntarily decided to quit as a primary dealer in <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> government securities and to discontinue most trading of the securities because the activities have not been profitable enough The company said in a statement `` the return on capital devoted to its government securities operations was insufficient to warrant continuation of the business.'' <PERSON> Rothschild </PERSON> said it had ample capital to satisfy new guidelines announced by the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> last November and the decision was made purely on profitability grounds. The guidelines announced by the <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> Fed Nov. 17 doubled the minimum capital required for securities companies who have the coveted title of primary dealer. The minimum was raised to more than $ 50 million. Primary dealers can buy and sell <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> government securities directly from the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fed </ORGANIZATION>. Through the buying and selling of the securities, the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> System </ORGANIZATION> seeks to influence interest rates. Therefore, financial firms with primary dealer status have an insight into government interest rate policy. Also, primary dealership is sought-after because some big institutional investors prefer to conduct their business exclusively through primary dealers. The <ORGANIZATION> L.F. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rothschild </ORGANIZATION> move, which will result in the loss of about 50 employees' jobs, curtails all of the company's sales and trading activities of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> government securities except for proprietary trading, meaning for its own account. The company had been acting as a primary dealer for about two years. From now on, <ORGANIZATION> Rothschild </ORGANIZATION>'s operations will consist of fixed-income securities sales and trading as a dealer in mortgage-backed securites, as well as corporate and high-yield securities. It will also continue to operate in the investment banking field. The withdrawal of <PERSON> L.F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Rothschild </PERSON>, a unit of <ORGANIZATION> Franklin </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Savings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> based in <LOCATION> Ottawa </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Kansas </LOCATION>, reduces the number of primary dealers to 44. On Friday, <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> NatWest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Government </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> announced its departure from the exclusive group. County NatWest, a subsidiary of <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>'s largest bank, <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Westminster </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION>, had been under pressure from the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fed </ORGANIZATION> to boost its capital.
