<HEAD>Goodyear Expects Earnings Drop</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Goodyear </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tire </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Rubber </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> on Tuesday projected a 53 percent decline in its 1988 fourth-quarter earnings from continuing operations and attributed the anticipated drop to a soft domestic tire market. The company estimated that 1988 fourth-quarter earnings from continuing operations would be 53 percent lower than the $ 119.4 million recorded for the same period in 1987. A previous company estimate projected earnings for that quarter at 40 percent to 45 percent lower than the fourth quarter of 1987. Tax charges from unusual items are expected to be approximately $ 26 million, rather than $ 33 million previously estimated, the company said. <ORGANIZATION> Goodyear </ORGANIZATION> will announce its fourth-quarter and 1988 results Feb. 14.
